## Deployment

- Production server: `49.234.112.108` (SSH user: `ubuntu`) ‚Äî see `DEPLOYMENT.md`
- App root on server: `/opt/pulsewatch`
- External access: **HTTP port 80** via Nginx (`http://49.234.112.108`, not HTTPS)
- PostgreSQL on port **6541** (existing server instance)

### Deploy commands

| Change scope | Command |
|---|---|
| Frontend only | `cd deploy && node redeploy-web.js` |
| API + frontend | `cd deploy && node deploy.js` |
| Nginx config | `cd deploy && node apply-nginx.js` |

## Workflow (required after feature fixes)

When completing a user-facing fix or feature:

1. Run `npm run test:unit` (and `npm run test:integration` if API changed)
2. **Commit** with a descriptive message (why, not just what)
3. **Push** to GitHub: `git push origin main`
4. **Deploy** to production using the table above
5. Verify: `http://49.234.112.108/en` returns 200

Do not skip push or deploy unless the user explicitly asks to hold off.

## Monitors CRUD

- Create: `/monitors/new` ‚Üí POST
- Edit: `/monitors/[id]/edit` ‚Üí PATCH (name, targetUrl, intervalSeconds; type is read-only)
- Detail: `/monitors/[id]` (read-only + Edit button)
- List actions: edit, pause/resume, delete

